Chet<br>
Where have you been, look again at the threads we have recently posted, Lost innocence was defecated upon by little barry spatz before it could produce the dialog it was intended to draw. Spatz has had several threads dedicated to the problems he has caused #47, 67 etc. long before I arrived. You are right when we began to have serious discussions the little commie shows up pees all over the place and off we go. <br><br>
There are times when we began to discuss some serious stuff here and it does get too heavy, I have had to back off on more then one occasion because I felt uneasy in exploring further in the direction where we were going and so MTF, SW, Art or others also seem to sense it and back off as well. We throw in humor which was typical of how we also dealt with hurtful situations in Nam.<br><br>
But back off and look at the threads that have been posted over the past few months and you will see the emergence of some very constructive and very central dialogs that any educator, student of the war or Vietnam vet would greatly benefit from reading. The treads include the humor and off the wall dialogs we have engaged in. There is no doult in my mind that what has been produced here would make a  very interesting book that reveals much of what we encountered in Nam and afterwards. <br>
Look at Ed’s poetry which he hasn’t posted since cybergook attacked him. Spatz also buried another poet by assigning him to a thread that died as soon as the poems more to spatz liking were posted. <br>
 <br>
The thing is we have not fallen under his control and begin threads to cover subjects we are interested in. Look at what I have recently posted, they are a dialog revealing much of what I did then and what I am doing now. The cook that was then and what I am today, you can see the same of Ed and SW and Art. It is all there I have learned a lot. <br>
Learned how the war affected me and how I have chosen to handle some of those encounters and how I have dealt with the new awareness this threads have awaken, thread #125 is the latest example where we take the negative for which the thread was started under and where the discussion builds into a new voice, and into a new dialog that give birth to new threads. Yes, its all scattered and a good editor could do much with what we have posted, an index would be great. But the threads should not be erased, edited or categorize under the topics they cover because that would mean the spirit of our discussions would be lost. Yes, this is the type of book many Vietnam and educators would drop $17.95 to purchase.  The problem is if there is a problem with it, is that its all scattered just like a good book that gives you all that information but not all at once.<br>
In War and Peace<br>
cookie<br>

